<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Verse (mm. 1–8): Light 2-note RH (6ths and 3rds). LH in open root position "33".
  m.7 uses quartal "44" I voicing (F-Bb-F) for open, airy color.
  m.8 uses "34" 2nd inversion for variety before the refrain.
- Refrain "Gloria" (mm. 9–14, 15–21): Fuller texture — 3-note RH added in repeat.
  m.15 LH gains 4th note (added 7th) for ii7 and Gm7 richness.
  m.19: one chord per beat — drive toward final cadence.
  IΔ7 voicing preserves the maj7 color (E3 in bass against F root).

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Refrain alto line (RH upper voice): C5→Bb4→A4→G4 (mm. 9–11) stepwise descent.
- LH bass roots: F→C→F→F→C→F / D→G→C→F→Bb→C / F→Bb→C→F — smooth dominant arcs.
- m.12 suspension: RH E4→C4 resolves the 4-3 suspension over V pedal.
- m.20 RH descends from F5→C5→A4 across final I landing.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1–4: 2-voice opening, single LH chord per bar — light and bright
- mm. 5–8: RH arpeggio in m.5 adds momentum, quartal color in m.7
- mm. 9–14: Refrain — fuller LH (4 notes), RH motion every half bar
- mm. 15–18: Refrain repeat — RH gains 3-note chords, LH 7th color
- mm. 19–21: Fast harmonic rhythm (1/beat) drive to full root-position close
-->
